 \frac{y}{xy} \left(\frac{1}{y}\frac{x - 1}{xy - 1} + \frac{y - 1}{y}\frac{x}{xy - 1}\right) = \frac{x - 1 + x(y - 1)}{xy(xy - 1)} = \frac{x - 1 + xy - x}{xy(xy - 1)} = \frac{xy - 1}{xy(xy - 1)} = \frac{1}{xy} 
